Both required files were emitted in the bundle directory and the transcript validates against the schema (25 iterations, 30 hypotheses, 28 analyses).

**Headline finding:** `feature_008` is the assigned treatment (40.2% prevalence, well-balanced across all other features — consistent with randomization). Marginally it raises `objective_response` from 0.16 to 0.36 (+0.20 absolute). But that average masks dramatic heterogeneity: the effect is concentrated in the subgroup `feature_013=0 AND feature_015=0 AND feature_021=0 AND feature_027=0` (n=15,681; 31% of cohort), where response rises from 0.17 to 0.80 — a +0.63 absolute risk difference, OR ≈ 17, with a logistic T×favorable interaction coefficient of +2.89 (p<1e-300). Outside that subgroup the risk difference is +0.008 (not significant). Each of the four modifiers is individually necessary; setting any one to 1 collapses the treatment effect. No additional within-favorable modifier (continuous or binary) survives Bonferroni correction. `feature_001`, `feature_022`, `feature_020`, and `feature_024` are prognostic but not predictive; ~19 features are uninformative noise.
